<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="167" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/803.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The advance loan has been agreed to upon the following among other
                                conditions: that the banks have option to provide further advances
                                for monthly requirements of the Chinese Government, which shall
                                assure to the groups option of undertaking reorganization loan.</p>
                            <p>In note of March 9, Yuan agreed to these conditions, but on the 14th
                                Tong signed a loan with a Belgian-Russian group for £1,000,000 at 97
                                and 5 per cent interest, with Kalgan Railway revenues as security
                                and option on £10,000,000 loan.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>